'''Benjamin Asare''' (born 13 July 1992) is a Ghanaian professional footballer who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Accra Hearts of Oak]] in the [[Ghana Premier League]] and the [[Ghana national football team|Ghana national team]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Otto Addo declares Benjamin Asare Ghana’s number one goalkeeper - MyJoyOnline |url=https://www.myjoyonline.com/otto-addo-declares-benjamin-asare-ghanas-number-one-goalkeeper/ |access-date=2025-08-15 |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-03-20 |title=FEATURE: Otto Addo, Take a Bold Step - Start Hearts of Oak goalkeeper Benjamin Asare against Chad |url=https://ghanasoccernet.com/feature-otto-addo-take-a-bold-step-start-hearts-of-oak-goalkeeper-benjamin-asare-against-chad |access-date=2025-08-15 |website=GhanaSoccernet |language=en}}</ref>

He rose to prominence in the Ghana Premier League through his performances for [[Accra Great Olympics]] before joining Hearts of Oak. In 2025 he earned his first call-up to the Ghana national team during the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]] qualification campaign.<ref name="ghanasoccernet">{{cite web |title=Benjamin Asare shines in Black Stars debut with back-to-back clean sheets |url=https://ghanasoccernet.com/benjamin-asare-shines-in-black-stars-debut-with-back-to-back-clean-sheets-against-chad-and-madagascar |publisher=GhanaSoccernet}}</ref>

==Club career==

=== Early career ===
Asare began his professional career with Sporting Mirren in 2017. He later joined Accra City Stars in 2018, where he continued his development as a goalkeeper in Ghanaian domestic football.

=== Accra Great Olympics ===
In 2020, Asare signed for [[Accra Great Olympics]]. During his time at the club he established himself as one of the reliable goalkeepers in the [[Ghana Premier League]]. His performances for the club attracted attention from larger clubs in the league.

=== Accra Hearts of Oak ===
In July 2024, Asare joined [[Accra Hearts of Oak]], ahead of the 2023–24 season.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-07-26 |title=Hearts of Oak announce signing of former Olympic goalkeeper Benjamin Asare |url=https://ghanasoccernet.com/hearts-of-oak-announce-signing-of-former-olympic-goalkeeper-benjamin-asare |access-date=2025-08-15 |website=GhanaSoccernet |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Mintah |first=Yaw Loic |last2=Mintah |first2=Yaw Loic |date=2024-07-26 |title=GPL: Hearts of Oak sign former Great Olympics goalkeeper Benjamin Asare - Citi Sports Online |url=https://citisportsonline.com/2024/07/gpl-hearts-of-oak-sign-former-great-olympics-goalkeeper-benjamin-asare/ |access-date=2025-08-15 |language=en-US}}</ref> During the 2024–25 season he emerged as one of the standout goalkeepers in the league, keeping 12 clean sheets in 18 league matches and earning recognition for his performances.<ref>{{cite web |title=Benjamin Asare named Goalkeeper of the Month |url=https://www.ghanafa.org/benjamin-asare-named-goalkeeper-of-the-month-for-september |publisher=Ghana Football Association}}</ref>

In April 2025, Hearts of Oak extended his contract until 2027, following his impressive performances for both club and country.<ref>{{cite web |title=Benjamin Asare signs contract extension with Hearts of Oak |url=https://www.gbcghanaonline.com/news/benjamin-asare-signs-two-year-extension-with-accra-hearts-of-oak/2025 |publisher=GBC Ghana}}</ref> The following month, he was named Ghana Premier League Goalkeeper of the Month after keeping three clean sheets in five matches.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Association |first=Ghana Football |title=Hearts of Oak’s Benjamin Asare wins May/June goalkeeper of the month |url=https://www.ghanafa.org/hearts-of-oaks-benjamin-asare-wins-may-june-goalkeeper-of-the-month |access-date=2025-08-15 |website=www.ghanafa.org |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-06-23 |title=Hearts of Oak’s Benjamin Asare named Best Goalkeeper for May/June |url=https://ghanasoccernet.com/hearts-of-oaks-benjamin-asare-named-best-goalkeeper-for-may-june |access-date=2025-08-15 |website=GhanaSoccernet |language=en}}</ref> In 2025, Benjamin Asare was named Male Home-Based Footballer of the Year at the 50th Sports Writers Association of Ghana (SWAG) Awards, recognising his standout performances for Accra Hearts of Oak and in the Black Stars setup during the season.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-11-16 |title=Antoine Semenyo, Benjamin Asare win big at 50th SWAG Awards |url=https://www.gbcghanaonline.com/sports/antoine-semenyo-benjamin-asare-win-big-at-50th-swag-awards/2025/ |access-date=2026-01-14 |language=en-US}}</ref>

==International career==
Asare received his first call-up to the [[Ghana national football team]] in March 2025 for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]] qualification matches against Chad and Madagascar.<ref>{{cite web |title=Fans react to Hearts of Oak goalkeeper Benjamin Asare's Ghana debut |url=https://ghanasoccernet.com/fans-react-to-hearts-of-oak-goalkeeper-benjamin-asares-ghana-debut |publisher=GhanaSoccernet}}</ref>

He made his international debut in a 5–0 victory against Chad, keeping a clean sheet.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Association |first=Ghana Football |title=Benjamin Asare starts in goal, Jordan Ayew leads the attack as Otto Addo names lineup for Chad clash |url=https://www.ghanafa.org/benjamin-asare-starts-in-goal-jordan-ayew-leads-the-attack-as-otto-addo-names-lineup-for-chad-clash |access-date=2025-08-15 |website=www.ghanafa.org |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-03-24 |title=Benjamin Asare shines in Black Stars debut with back-to-back clean sheets against Chad and Madagascar |url=https://ghanasoccernet.com/benjamin-asare-shines-in-black-stars-debut-with-back-to-back-clean-sheets-against-chad-and-madagascar |access-date=2025-08-15 |website=GhanaSoccernet |language=en}}</ref> He also kept another clean sheet in Ghana’s subsequent win against Madagascar during the qualifiers.

